{
  "texts": [
    "However, modeling essay organization faces challenges due to the limited capability of models to represent the essay's organization and relate that representation to organization quality.",
    "In their work, Song et al. (2020a) proposed an approach to represent and evaluate the notion of organization in argumentative essays using sentence-and paragraph-level discourse elements.",
    "These elements help identify the functions of sentences and paragraphs, such as introduction, thesis, main idea, evidence, elaboration, or conclusion.",
    "In this study, the authors designed a multi-task model that jointly learns sentence function identification and paragraph function identification for organization evaluation.",
    "As it is shown in Fig. 13, Bi-LSTM is used to represent sentence-level essay features, and positional information is incorporated to form a representation of sentence functions."
  ]
}